talked a few=20
times around here about TNB USA Inc., a proposed explicitly narrow bank (TN=
B stands for =E2=80=9CThe Narrow Bank=E2=80=9D) that has tried to get appro=
ved by the Fed, so far without success.


  [5] Intuitively the reason it would be unsustainable is something like =
=E2=80=9Cif a stock is at $20, and you keep buying until it hits $100, lots=
 of people who owned it at $20 will become sellers at $100, and you=E2=80=
=99ll run out of borrowing capacity before you can buy all their stock.=E2=
=80=9D In the event, what=20
seems to have blown up Archegos is that one of the *issuers* of the stocks,=
 ViacomCBS Inc., became a seller at the high prices that Hwang created, iss=
uing new stock and causing the stock to gap down, leading to margin calls a=
nd the end of Archegos.


  [6] It=E2=80=99s=20
roughly=20
what got Avi Eisenberg=20
last month (though, for crypto).


  [7] As=20
I said when the charges were first brought, he=E2=80=99s also accused of *l=
ying* to the banks, which is (1) a separate crime, (2) easier to prove, and=
 (3) not a good look vis-a-vis the manipulation charges.


  [8] It apparently was shared by an employee on LinkedIn, making it even b=
etter.


  [9] I=E2=80=99m being hyperbolic. He didn=E2=80=99t actually sell it for =
$47 billion, but he extracted plenty of value for himself at valuations lik=
e that, and he=E2=80=99s not really going to buy it back for $0, but he has=
 been trying to buy it out of bankruptcy.


  [10] See Rule 203(b)(2)(iv) of Regulation SHO, which exempts security fut=
ures from the locate requirement. A =E2=80=9C=E2=80=98security future=E2=80=
=99 means a contract of sale for future delivery of a single security.=E2=
=80=9D


