not subject to *capital* regulation because of their *liquidity* risk: They=
=E2=80=99re subject to *liquidity* regulation because of that risk. But it =
does not pay to be too pure about this stuff; whenever there=E2=80=99s a ru=
n on a bank, people talk about the need for stricter capital requirements, =
